# Maps for the registration form and your website

CSA Admin can now show depot maps in two places:

- on the registration form, to help future members find and select their depot;
- on your public website, to share the same depot map with visitors.

You can enable and configure these maps from the [maps settings](/settings#maps).

To make the first setup easier, all depots with usable addresses have been geocoded when possible. Geocoding means turning an address into map coordinates (lat/lng). It is a helpful starting point, but it can place a marker on a nearby street or building, so it is still recommended to check each depot position before showing it on maps.

Take a few minutes to review your depots on [the depots page](/depots): open each depot, verify or adjust the marker, then enable **Visible on maps**. You can also select several depots and use the batch actions to show or hide them on maps.

The new [Maps handbook](/handbook/maps) explains how to enable the registration map, add the public map to your website, customize it, and prepare your depots step by step.

Feel free to [contact me](/support) if you need help setting this up or notice anything unusual.
